'''G<U+00E9>rard Xavier Marcel Depardieu''' ({{IPA-fr|<U+0292>e<U+0281>a<U+0281> d<U+0259>pa<U+0281>dj<U+00F8>|lang|fr-Gerard_Depardieu.ogg}}; born 27 December 1948) is a <!--please don't add RUSSIAN, go to talk page first--> French <!--please don't add RUSSIAN, go to talk page first-->actor, film-maker, businessman and vineyard owner. He is one of the most prolific character actors in film history, having completed approximately 170 movies since 1967.  He has twice won the [[C<U+00E9>sar Award]] for Best Actor as well as the [[Golden Globe]] award for Best Actor in ''[[Green Card (film)|Green Card]]''. After he garnered huge critical acclaim for the title role in ''[[Cyrano de Bergerac (1990 film)|Cyrano de Bergerac]]'', which landed him a nomination for an [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]], Depardieu acted in many big budget [[Hollywood]] movies. He is a Chevalier of the [[L<U+00E9>gion d'honneur]] and Chevalier of the [[Ordre national du M<U+00E9>rite]]. He was granted citizenship of [[Russia]] in January 2013, made an honorary citizen of [[Belgium]] in August 2013, and the same year became a cultural ambassador of [[Montenegro]].

==Early life==
G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu was born in [[Ch<U+00E2>teauroux]], [[Indre]], [[France]]. He is one of the five children of Anne Jeanne Jos<U+00E8>phe (n<U+00E9>e Marillier) and Ren<U+00E9> Maxime Lionel Depardieu, a metal worker and volunteer fireman.<ref name="filmreference1948">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/74/Gerard-Depardieu.html |title=Gerard Depardieu Biography (1948<U+2013>) |publisher=Filmreference.com |accessdate=26 February 2010}}</ref><ref name="genindre1">{{cite web |url=http://genindre.org/arbpdf/depardieu.pdf |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20081030112220/http://genindre.org/arbpdf/depardieu.pdf |archivedate=30 October 2008 |title=Les anc<U+00EA>tres de G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu (1948) }}</ref>

Depardieu spent more time on the street than in the classroom and left school at 12.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/mlanie-laurent---in-it-for-the-drama-and-the-danger-2015917.html|accessdate=8 December 2011 |location=London |work=The Independent |title=M<U+00E9>lanie Laurent&nbsp;<U+2013> In it for the drama and the danger|date=2 July 2010}}</ref>{{not in source|date=October 2013}}

==Acting career==
At the age of 16, Depardieu left Ch<U+00E2>teauroux for [[Paris]]. There, he began acting in the new comedy theatre [[Caf<U+00E9> de la Gare]], along with [[Patrick Dewaere]], Romain Bouteille, [[Sotha (actress)|Sotha]], [[Coluche]], and [[Miou-Miou]].<ref>[http://www.lexpress.fr/culture/scene/theatre/30-ans-toutes-ses-dents_498236.html 30th Anniversary of Caf<U+00E9> de la Gare], [[L'Express (France)|L'Express]], 15 August 2002, (in French)</ref> He studied dancing under Jean-Laurent Cochet, and went on to become one of France's most renowned actors. 

His breakout film role came in 1974 playing Jean-Claude in [[Bertrand Blier]]'s comedy ''[[Going Places (1974 film)|Les Valseuses]]'' (''Going Places'').<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/list/9baDvZc-KPA/ G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu at IMDb]</ref> Other prominent early roles include a starring role alongside [[Robert DeNiro]] in [[Bernardo Bertolucci]]'s historical epic ''[[1900 (film)|1900]]'' (1976) and a role in [[Fran<U+00E7>ois Truffaut]]'s ''[[The Last Metro]]'' (1980), for which he was nominated for a C<U+00E9>sar Award.

In 1986, his international fame grew as a result of his performance as a doomed, hunchbacked farmer in the film ''[[Jean de Florette]]''.  Five years later he won a ''[[C<U+00E9>sar Award|C<U+00E9>sar]]'' for his starring role in ''[[Cyrano de Bergerac (1990 film)|Cyrano de Bergerac]]'', for which he was also nominated for an Academy Award. This is still considered by many to be his most notable role.
[[File:G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu Carole Bouquet 2001.jpg|thumb|upright|Depardieu with [[Carole Bouquet]] at the [[2001 Cannes Film Festival]].]]
[[File:G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu and Vladimir Putin, Sochi, Russia, 2013-01-06 1.jpeg|thumb|upright|G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu and Vladimir Putin, [[Sochi]], Russia, January 5, 2013.]]
[[File:G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu Cannes 1994.jpg|thumb|upright|Depardieu at the [[1994 Cannes Film Festival]]]]

In 1990, Gerard crossed over into the American film market by co-starring in [[Peter Weir]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Green Card (film)|Green Card]]'', for which he won a Golden Globe Award. He has since had other roles in other English-language films, including [[Ridley Scott]]'s ''[[1492: Conquest of Paradise]]'' (1992), [[Kenneth Branagh]]'s ''[[Hamlet (1996 movie)|Hamlet]]'' (1996), and [[Ang Lee]]'s ''[[Life of Pi (film)|Life of Pi]]'' (2012).

More recently, he has played [[Obelix|Ob<U+00E9>lix]] in the four live-action ''[[Asterix films (live action)|Ast<U+00E9>rix]]'' movies in which he is said to have discovered [[M<U+00E9>lanie Laurent]] when she was 14.<ref name="gede">{{Cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/europe/this-europe-confessions-of-depardieu-597202.html |title=This Europe: Confessions of Depardieu |work=The Independent |location=UK |date=10 February 2003 |accessdate=26 February 2010  | first=John | last=Lichfield}}{{dead link|date=January 2013}}</ref>

In 2009 he took part in a rare performance of Sardou's ''[[La Haine (drama)|La Haine]]'' at the Festival de Radio France et Montpellier Languedoc Roussillon, with [[Fanny Ardant]]; subsequently broadcast on [[France Musique]].<ref>[http://www.festivalradiofrancemontpellier.com/2009/19-la-haine-ardant-depardieu-onm.php Presentation of concert on Festival de Radio France site.]</ref>

==Personal life==
In 1970, Depardieu married [[<U+00C9>lisabeth Depardieu|<U+00C9>lisabeth Guignot]], with whom he had two children, actor [[Guillaume Depardieu|Guillaume]] (1971<U+2013>2008) and actress [[Julie Depardieu|Julie]] (1973). On 28 January 1992, while separated from <U+00C9>lisabeth, he had a daughter, Roxanne, with the model Karine Sylla. In 1996 he divorced <U+00C9>lisabeth and began a relationship with actress [[Carole Bouquet]], who was his partner from 1997 to 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dhnet.be/culture/people/article/128735/bouquet-depardieu-en-crise.html |title=Bouquet&nbsp;<U+2014> Depardieu en crise |publisher=Dhnet.be |date=31 August 2005 |accessdate=26 February 2010}}</ref>

On 14 July 2006, he had a son, Jean, with French-Cambodian H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Bizot (daughter of [[Fran<U+00E7>ois Bizot]] and not to be confused with actress [[H<U+00E9>l<U+00E8>ne Bizot]]), according to the issue 3089 (31 July 2008) of ''[[Paris Match]]'' and the [[Phnom Penh Post]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.phnompenhpost.com/index.php/2011042248640/Siem-Reap-Insider/upheaval-of-life-blamed-on-apsara.html |title=Upheaval of life blamed on Apsara |work=The Phnom Penh Post |location=Cambodia |date=22 April 2011 |accessdate=25 April 2011  | first1=Michael | last1=Sloan}}</ref> Since 2005, Depardieu has lived with a [[Harvard University|Harvard]]-educated novelist, Cl<U+00E9>mentine Igou.

On 13 October 2008, his son Guillaume, whose health had been severely affected by drugs, a motorbike crash and, most importantly, a hospital infection contracted during the post-accident operations, eventually leading to the amputation of his leg, died at the age of 37 from complications linked to a sudden case of [[pneumonia]].<ref>{{cite news | first = John | last = Lichfield | title = G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu's son dies of pneumonia at 37 | date = 14 October 2008 | url = http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/grard-depardieus-son-dies-of-pneumonia-at-37-960265.html | work = The Independent | accessdate = 3 January 2013}}</ref>

In recent years, Depardieu has attracted attention from the media and legal authorities for his behavior.  In August 2012, he was accused of assault and battery for punching a motorist in Paris.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2012/aug/17/gerard-gepardieu-accused-road-rage-assault |title=G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu accused of punching motorist in road rage assault |author=Henry Barnes |work=guardian.co.uk |date=17 August 2012}}</ref>  In November 2012, he was arrested for driving while intoxicated after he fell from his scooter, and was found to have a blood alcohol level of 1.8 grams per litre, well above the French limit for driving of 0.5.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2240547/French-actor-Gerard-Depardieu-arrested-driving-scooter-drunk-Paris-following-minor-accident.html |title=French actor Gerard Depardieu 'arrested for driving scooter drunk' in Paris following minor accident |author=Kimberley Dadds |date=29 November 2012 |work=DailyMail}}</ref>

He has been an official resident of [[Estaimpuis|N<U+00E9>chin]], [[Belgium]] since 7 December 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=Fraser |first=Christian |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-20760572 |title=Depardieu: French film star stirs tax row |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=2012-12-17 |accessdate=2013-01-25}}</ref> French prime minister [[Jean-Marc Ayrault]] criticised his move.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-20691889|title=Depardieu tax exile move 'shabby' - French PM Ayrault |work=[[BBC]] |date=12 December 2012 |accessdate=17 December 2012}}</ref>  On 15 December 2012, Depardieu publicly stated he was handing back his French passport.<ref>{{cite news |title=Depardieu 'to give up passport' in tax exile row |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-20750593|newspaper=BBC news |date=16 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lejdd.fr/Politique/Actualite/Gerard-Depardieu-Je-rends-mon-passeport-581254 |date=15 December 2012 |work=lejdd.fr |title=G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu : "Je rends mon passeport"}}</ref> On 3 January 2013, Russian President [[Vladimir Putin]] signed an Executive Order granting Russian citizenship to Depardieu.<ref>{{cite news|title=Executive Order on granting Russian citizenship to Gerard Depardieu|url=http://eng.kremlin.ru/news/4833 |date=January 3, 2013 |work=Russian Presidential Executive Office}}</ref> Depardieu soon returned the favor by attacking Putin's critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/europe/2013/01/20131145231670149.html |title=Depardieu attacks Russia's opposition. |publisher=Aljazeera.com |date= |accessdate=2013-01-25}}</ref>  Depardieu was made an honorary citizen of Belgium in August 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=G<U+00E9>rard Depardieu is awarded Belgian citizenship|url=http://www.theguardian.com/film/2013/aug/29/gerard-depardieu-belgian-citizenship-passport |date=August 29, 2013 |work=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref>

==Awards==
Depardieu has been nominated for the Best Actor in a Leading Role [[C<U+00E9>sar award|C<U+00E9>sar]] 15 times during his career and won it twice, in 1981 and 1991. He was also nominated for an Oscar in 1990 for his role in ''[[Cyrano de Bergerac (1990 film)|Cyrano de Bergerac]]''.

*1981: ''[[C<U+00E9>sar Award for Best Actor]]'' for his role in ''[[The Last Metro]]'' (Le dernier m<U+00E9>tro)
*1985: ''[[Venice Film Festival]] Award'' for best actor for his role in ''[[Police (1985 film)|Police]]''
*1985: ''Chevalier'' (Knight) of the [[Ordre national du M<U+00E9>rite]]
*1990: ''[[Cannes Film Festival]]'': [[Best Actor Award (Cannes Film Festival)|Best actor]] award for his role in ''[[Cyrano de Bergerac (1990 film)|Cyrano de Bergerac]]''
*1991: ''C<U+00E9>sar Award for Best Actor'' for his role in ''[[Cyrano de Bergerac (1990 film)|Cyrano de Bergerac]]''
*1991: ''[[Golden Globe Award]]'' for Best Actor for his role in ''[[Green Card (film)|Green Card]]''
*1996: ''Chevalier'' (Knight) of the [[L<U+00E9>gion d'honneur]].<ref name="jorf19960102">
